[Additionally, Molbak, et al. (1) note that PT 14b is one of the phage types
of enterica serotype enteritidis that, at least in Denmark, is often
associated with, imported poultry products including broiler chickens. Of
note, they reported that 2/12 strains were fluoroquinolone resistant.
It is important to note that identical phage typing analysis does not
necessarily suggest identity. Fadl et al. (2) found that arbitrarily primed
PCR analysis found distinct amplified DNA patterns with isolates of
identical phage type, including 14b.
1. Molbak K, Gerner-Smidt P, Wegener HC: Increasing quinolone resistance in
_Salmonella enterica_ serotype enteritidis. Emerg Infect Dis 2002; 8:
514-15.
2. Fadl AA, Nguyen AV, Khan MI: Analysis of _Salmonella enteritidis_
isolates by arbitarily primed PCR. J Clin Microbiol 1995; 33:987-89.
- Mod.LL]
